01:06:47.000 --> 01:07:03.000
The company was designed with the help of an advertising agency and placed on the central television.

01:07:03.000 --> 01:07:18.000
When this study was carried out, the results were analyzed, a report was made on the study. We went to present the results of this research project to the company's customer.

01:07:18.000 --> 01:07:41.000
We contacted the commercial director of this manufacturer, a well-developed and well-educated person. However, there were many specialists at the presentation, including the president of the company, the head and the owner.

01:07:42.000 --> 01:08:01.000
During the presentation, which lasted about 30 minutes, all the main results of the study were presented. It was clear how the listeners react, either by asking questions or by offering their own forms of decision-making.

01:08:01.000 --> 01:08:27.000
The presentation was positive. It was clear that the customer liked our research, and most importantly, that they saw new conceptual conclusions that they did not know about their target audience, preferences, loyalty to their brand, perception of this brand by consumers.

01:08:27.000 --> 01:08:47.000
Only one person was silent. When the last point was set, when we said that we were ready to answer all the questions, this person, who was an analyst of the marketing department, asked us a question that put us in a deadlock.

01:08:47.000 --> 01:09:10.000
Why was a specific method of research used in this project? Why the whole test? Why not home surveys? He said that a few years ago he personally collected 150 surveys, interviewing housewives who lived near the factory.

01:09:10.000 --> 01:09:34.000
Imagine a situation when two years ago researchers and employees tried to invite respondents who were at home after a hard working day, and then on a trip to the subway or in Moscow traffic jams, to a survey about the perception of the brand, the use of the mayonnaise brand at home.

01:09:34.000 --> 01:09:48.000
Who will open the closed door of the entrance or the door of the apartment? Almost no one. I think that the percentage of responses in such a survey will be zero.

01:09:48.000 --> 01:10:09.000
