01:15:56.000 --> 01:16:20.000
At first glance, many listeners or managers do not see the difference between these two concepts, and often these two concepts are used as synonyms. Nevertheless, we say that data and information have differences in terms of their definition and in terms of the attitude to the adoption of marketing decisions.

01:16:20.000 --> 01:16:49.000
Data is unstructured, undetermined data that, of course, has a certain value, a certain value for the company. Nevertheless, it is just the volume, the scale, the numbers, statistics, data about sales, data from competitors that can enter the information base, the information system of the organization, and which without special processing do not bear a specific value.

01:16:50.000 --> 01:17:08.000
While the information that can be obtained based on the analysis of these data has a more structured form, reduces the uncertainty that predisposes and reduces the risk of making management decisions.

01:17:08.000 --> 01:17:32.000
And in this regard, due to its structuring and reduction of uncertainty, it has its own value and value. Information that becomes important for various types of organizations or functional units within the organization that use this information.

01:17:32.000 --> 01:18:01.000
For example, if we now imagine the functional structure of the company management, if we talk about the main areas of activity in different departments that are part of the management of this company, then we can highlight such main functional areas of activity as production, finance, human resources, of course, as information technologies, marketing, sales.

01:18:01.000 --> 01:18:20.000
And logistic operations, for example. In some organizations, especially those that produce and offer innovative products to the market, or products that are constantly being updated, there are also departments called research and development.

01:18:20.000 --> 01:18:43.000
Research, in which scientific, technological, engineering personnel accumulate, who are engaged in the development of concepts of new innovative products.

01:18:44.000 --> 01:19:00.000
They are engaged in research and direction of financial flows within the organization. They are engaged in the direct production of products, the storage of this product, and the shipment to consumers.

01:19:00.000 --> 01:19:20.000
They are engaged in contacts with consumers. This is the sales department. And still, of all the listed units, the only department that carries out an analytical function and is engaged in the analysis of external incoming information and the analysis of the external environment is the marketing department.

01:19:20.000 --> 01:19:33.000
From the marketing department to the production department, information can be received about the preferences of consumers, about the claims of consumers to certain characteristics of the product, to certain attributes of the product.

01:19:33.000 --> 01:19:48.000
And in turn, from the production department to the marketing department, information is received about the number of produced products, about the characteristics of certain items or the names of the categories of products that are produced, and so on.

01:19:48.000 --> 01:20:10.000
From the marketing department, information is received about the prices for the products of competitors, in order to analyze the cost of the product, as well as to determine flexible prices that will be competitive to competitors.

01:20:10.000 --> 01:20:35.000
From the financial department to the marketing department, information is received about the cost of the product, about the constant and variable costs and opportunities for the use of various price strategies, depending on the stage of the life cycle of the product or how it is positioned in relation to competitors.

01:20:35.000 --> 01:20:48.000
From the logistics department to the marketing department, information is received about the quantity and composition of the produced products, about the assortment of the produced products.

01:20:48.000 --> 01:21:15.000
From the logistics department to the marketing department, information is received about the quantity of the products that are stored in warehouses, or, on the contrary, which type of products is more in demand, and which type of products requires intervention or the creation of special marketing programs for their promotion.

01:21:15.000 --> 01:21:38.000
Data and information are different. Data has a lower value and cost for the company. It is an unstructured volume of various information, various data, facts and figures that are received by the analytical department of the company.

01:21:38.000 --> 01:21:57.000
As a result of the data processing process and adding additional values to this data in the form of structuring, in the form of reducing uncertainty, their value increases, and this data takes the form of marketing information, which is the basis for making marketing decisions.

01:21:57.000 --> 01:22:21.000
