01:23:31.000 --> 01:23:59.000
on the basis of which you can get data about fluctuations in demand for a certain commodity category, about average prices for a commodity category in different trading networks, about an average check per week or an average check on a certain day of the week in order to smooth out periods of surge or drop in demand for certain commodity groups, and so on.

01:23:59.000 --> 01:24:12.000
This information, which is received in the form of large, long Excel tables, will be data for a specific manufacturer.

01:24:12.000 --> 01:24:25.000
By the way, if we talk about the cost of a full subscription to the AC Nielsen Retail Audit, then such a subscription can cost up to $ 100,000 per year.

01:24:25.000 --> 01:24:54.000
This information is not verified and unstructured data, which can be converted into structured data by various methods of selecting the necessary information.

01:24:54.000 --> 01:25:14.000
For example, the demand for confectionery products is carried out in trading networks that operate in a discount format, that is, in the format of not very expensive trading networks where your products are presented and at the same time the products of competitors are presented.

